Â  <h3>ğŸ“Validator</h3>
Â  Â 
Â  <h4>Create Empower validator</h4>
Â  <p>Before creating a validator, you should make sure that the node is synchronised and check the balance of your wallet.</p>
Â  Â 
Â  <h5>Check synchronisation status</h5>
Â  <p>Once your node is fully synchronised, the output will read false.</p>
Â  Â 
Â  <pre>empowerd status 2>&1 \| jq .SyncInfo</pre>
Â  Â 
Â  <h5>Check your balance</h5>
Â  <pre>empowerd query bank balances $wallet_ADDRESS</pre>
Â   Â 
Â  <h5>Create validator</h5>
Â  <pre>empowerd tx staking create-validator \
Â  --amount 1000000umpwr \
Â  --from $wallet \
Â  --commission-max-change-rate "0.01" \
Â  --commission-max-rate "0.2" \
Â  --commission-rate "0.05" \
Â  --min-self-delegation "1" \
Â  --pubkey  $(empowerd tendermint show-validator) \
Â  --moniker [MONIKER] \
Â  --chain-id $empowerd \
Â  --gas auto \
Â  --gas-adjustment 1.3 \
Â  --fees 10000umpwr </pre>
Â  Â 
Â  <p>You can add the flags â€” website â€” security-contact â€” identity â€” details (optional)</p>
Â  Â 
Â  <pre>--website <WEB_SITE_URL> \
Â  --security-contact <YOUR_CONTACT> \
Â  --identity <KEYBASE_IDENTITY> \
Â  --details <YOUR_VALIDATOR_DETAILS></pre>
